RESULT: Continuity tests confirm intact wiring from Load Input Cable (+) to the Load Protection Diode and to both bulbs (main and indicator), with expected resistances. Voltage is present at the diode anode (0.3592 V) but drops to ~0 V at the cathode and at both bulbs. No hidden breaks or high-resistance faults are detected along the measured paths.
