2026-04-16 12:37:33 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['load protection diode (load module)'] hypothesis_explanation="Voltage is present at the anode of the load module's protection diode, but virtually zero voltage is observed at the cathode and across both bulbs. The continuity test confirms that wiring up to and from the diode is intact. The diode, however, drops nearly the entire voltage, suggesting it is internally open (failed open), only allowing a negligible leakage voltage to appear at the cathode and load side. This would block current to both bulbs, making them remain off even though input voltage is present. Previous tests confirm its forward voltage at test currents, but under the actual load, the diode appears not to conduct. Hence, the diode is suspected to be faulty (failed open under normal operating conditions)."
