description: Measure the voltage across the output terminals of the control module (the cables that supply the load module) to check if the relay is delivering 12V as expected when the lamp should be on., outcome="The voltage measured at 'Control Output Cable (+)' is 0.3592 V, and at 'Control Output Cable (−)' is 0.0003 V. The output voltage is significantly below the expected 12V when the lamp should be on. No polarity inversion detected in the cable assignments.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> switched cables at the input of the control module,
description: Measure the voltage across the input terminals of the control module to determine if the module is receiving the correct 12V supply from the power supply module., outcome='The voltage at Control Input Cable (+) is 11.9875\u202fV, and the voltage at Control Input Cable (−) is 0.0002\u202fV. These measurements confirm that the control module is receiving approximately 12\u202fV across its input terminals. No polarity inversion is detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> relay in control module,
description: Test the relay in the control module to see if it is switching correctly and delivering 12V to its output as required. Measure the voltage across the relay contacts and check if the relay is closing properly under low ambient light conditions., outcome="The inspection panel was successfully opened, and the relay's continuity is nominal with a measured resistance of 0.01 Ω. The voltage measured across the relay contacts is 11.99 V (positive) and 0.36 V (negative) relative to ground, indicating the relay is delivering near the expected 12V output. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> switched cables between control module and load module,
description: Test for continuity and voltage on the cables connecting the control module to the load module to determine if there is a break or high resistance in the cables or connectors., outcome='All cables show nominal continuity with measured resistances matching nominal values (0.1 Ω). Voltage readings are consistent: (+) cables show 0.3592 V, (−) cables show 0.0003 V. No breaks or high resistance detected in the cable connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=160.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> diode in load module,
description: Test the diode in the load module for proper functionality and check for a voltage drop across it to determine if it is blocking current when it should allow conduction., outcome='The diode test result for the load protection diode is nominal, with a forward voltage of 0.7 V, as expected. Measured voltage at the anode is 0.3592 V and at the cathode is 0.0003 V. There are no polarity inversions detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_diode', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> internal wiring (control module),
description: Visually inspect the internal wiring and connections in the control module, especially around the output terminals and relay output path, for loose connections, damaged wires, cold solder joints, or other physical faults., outcome='No loose connections, damaged wires, or physical faults were observed in the control module, relay, or output cables. All inspected components appear intact and connected, with no observable internal faults.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> internal wiring (load module),
description: Visually inspect the internal wiring and connections in the load module, especially around the input terminals, diode, bulbs, and any connectors, for loose connections, damaged wires, cold solder joints, or other physical faults., outcome='All inspected components, including the main load lamp, internal indicator lamp, load protection diode, and both input cables, show no observable internal faults or physical issues. Both bulbs are not lit. There are no noted polarity inversions in the observed cable connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> input terminals of the load module (at the component side, past the connectors),
description: Directly measure the voltage at the internal input terminals of the load module, after the connector but before the diode, to verify if voltage from the control module is arriving at the load module itself., outcome="Measured voltage at 'Load Input Cable (+)' is 0.3592 V and at 'Load Input Cable (−)' is 0.0003 V, both relative to ground. Voltage is present at the internal input terminals of the load module after the connector but before the diode. Polarity labeling matches between cables and no polarity inversion is observed.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> switched cables between power supply module and control module,
description: Test for continuity and measure the voltage across the cables connecting the power supply module to the control module to check for any subtle intermittent connection or voltage drop, especially since the power supply indicator is on but the control module output is low., outcome='All cables show nominal continuity with measured resistance matching the expected values. Voltage readings are consistent and as expected on both the power supply and control module input cables. No polarity inversion is detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=160.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> switched cables indicator LED (control module),
description: Test the functionality of the switched cables indicator LED in the control module by measuring the voltage across it when the relay is closed. Observe if it is lighting up and whether the voltage matches the expected value. This can help confirm if the issue is before or after the relay and whether the switching operation inside the module is functioning as expected., outcome='The control relay could not be closed, as it does not have a togglable function. The inspection panel was opened successfully. Voltage measured at the Ambient Light Sensor was 0.119\u202fV (positive) and 0.0003\u202fV (negative), and the sensor showed no observable internal fault.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('close_switch', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> power supply indicator LED (power supply module),
description: Measure the voltage across the power supply indicator LED and resistor, and check if the voltage at the battery terminals is consistent with power supply output. This checks if the battery is capable of providing sufficient current under load or if there's an issue with voltage sag or weak battery under load., outcome='The voltage at the battery terminals is 12.0 V, and the PSU output cable (+) measures 11.9876 V, which is very close, indicating minimal voltage sag under load. The voltage across the PSU status LED and resistor is consistent with proper operation. No polarity inversion is detected in your measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=110.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient light sensor and associated comparator circuitry (control module),
description: Test the ambient light sensor and its associated comparator circuit in the control module, measuring the sensor output voltage and the control signal at the comparator output during changing ambient light conditions. This will reveal if the control logic driving the relay is functioning as expected., outcome='The ambient light sensor shows nominal continuity (10 kΩ) and its output voltage is measured as 0.119 V (positive) with respect to ground. The control relay input is measured at 11.99 V (positive) and 0.36 V (negative) with respect to ground. No polarity inversion is detected in the measured cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=105.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module: internal wiring between input terminals and bulbs (before diode and after diode),
description: Test the continuity and voltage across the load module's internal wiring from the input terminals to the nodes before the diode, between the diode and the bulbs, and from there to the lamp terminals. This will check for hidden breaks or high resistance in each internal branch, as earlier voltage is present at the load module inputs but not across the bulbs., outcome='Continuity tests confirm intact wiring from Load Input Cable (+) to the Load Protection Diode and to both bulbs (main and indicator), with expected resistances. Voltage is present at the diode anode (0.3592 V) but drops to ~0 V at the cathode and at both bulbs. No hidden breaks or high-resistance faults are detected along the measured paths.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=185.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load Module (input terminals referenced to battery ground),
description: Measure the voltage at the load module's input terminals (both before and after the connector) with respect to the true battery ground (negative terminal) to check if there is a ground reference issue, floating segment, or potential difference being lost in grounding. Perform the same measurement for the output of the control module for comparison., outcome="All measured voltages are consistent: both the positive cables ('load_cable_pos' and 'ctrl_cable_out_pos') show approximately 0.36 V with respect to battery ground, while the negative cables ('load_cable_neg' and 'ctrl_cable_out_neg') are close to 0 V. No polarity inversion is detected in these connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
